# Tick Model

## Core Rule

The game is tick-based.

Current setting:

```text
1 real second = 1 game tick
Server Clock

The backend tracks:

last_processed_at
world.current_tick

When /world is requested, the backend calculates elapsed real time and processes the required number of game ticks.

Processing Rule

Only one normal read endpoint should process elapsed time:

GET /world

Write endpoints may process elapsed time before applying state changes:

POST /player/me/actions
POST /contracts/{contract_id}/accept
POST /player/me/movement/start

Most read endpoints must not process ticks:

GET /player/me
GET /player
GET /contracts
GET /market
GET /pvp/impacts
GET /stations
GET /routes
Why

The dashboard loads multiple endpoints per refresh. If every endpoint processes elapsed ticks, the world advances multiple ticks per second.

Frontend Rule

The frontend does not advance ticks manually.

The frontend refreshes state periodically and displays current tick, remaining action ticks and updated world state.

Debug Tick

POST /admin/tick may exist for development, but it is not part of normal gameplay.